<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Hardened Runtime entitlements for the bundled Python sidecar.

Load-bearing: ONLY com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation.

Reason (empty-entitlements retest, 28 Apr 2026 — RED):
PyInstaller bundled Python.framework carries an internal code seal
distinct from per-binary signatures. AMFI library validation reads
the framework nested seal at dlopen time, not the per-binary resign
sign-sidecar.sh applies. Result: dlopen of Python.framework Python
fails with mapping process and mapped file have different Team IDs,
even after a full remove-then-resign cycle across all inner Mach-Os
under a single Apple Distribution identity Z56GZVA2QB.

Full diagnostic + path forward in docs/private/c3-session-notes.md
section Empty-entitlements retest. Plan for a future attempt at
framework-level resigning in plans/c3-empty-ents-retest.md.

REQUIRED for the run/transcription path (added 7 Jun 2026 — crash RED→GREEN):
  cs.allow-jit + cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory.
The Apr 2026 "not needed" reasoning below was scoped to SERVE ONLY. The run
path transcribes via mlx-whisper, which pulls numba → llvmlite. llvmlite
JIT-compiles numba's DTW/word-timestamp kernels at runtime and makes the
mapped pages executable (llvm::sys::Memory::protectMappedMemory →
sys_icache_invalidate). Under Hardened Runtime without these two exceptions
the kernel SIGKILLs the process with EXC_BAD_ACCESS / "Code Signature Invalid"
(CODESIGNING Invalid Page) before transcription produces anything — surfaces
in the desktop as "Run failed (no terminus event) / unknown", with no output
dir created. Crash reports: ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/bristlenose-sidecar-*.ips.
The provider-resolution fix (same day) unmasked this: runs previously died at
LLM-validation preflight, before ever reaching transcription.

  cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables: still not required.

APP STORE / TestFlight REVIEW FLAG: both exceptions are legitimate for a
JIT-using dependency (numba) but are Hardened Runtime relaxations Apple Review
scrutinises. Route through the app-store-police agent before submitting. The
numba-free alternative (exclude numba, lose mlx-whisper word-level timestamps
→ breaks deep-linked transcript timecodes) was considered and rejected as a
worse trade; revisit only if Review pushes back.

Stale (Apr 2026, serve-only — kept for the audit trail):
  cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory: CPython 3.12 has no W+X.
  cs.allow-jit: ctranslate2 excluded, MLX uses Metal GPU not CPU JIT.

C3 credential path (Apr 2026): sidecar never accesses macOS Keychain.
Swift host fetches via Security.framework, injects BRISTLENOSE_*_API_KEY
env vars at subprocess launch. No Keychain entitlements needed here.

App Sandbox (14 Jul 2026, MAS upload gate): the nested sidecar now carries
com.apple.security.app-sandbox=true + com.apple.security.inherit=true so App
Store Connect accepts it and it inherits the host .app's sandbox at sublaunch.
User-facing sandbox resource entitlements (files.*, network.*) stay on the HOST
app only — never here (they'd trip the _libsecinit_appsandbox abort under inherit).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- MAS: every nested executable must declare app-sandbox=true or App Store
         Connect rejects the upload ("App sandbox not enabled"). -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>
    <!-- Inherit the host .app's sandbox container/profile. MUST accompany
         app-sandbox on a nested helper; the sidecar is only ever sublaunched
         by the sandboxed Bristlenose.app, so it has a parent to inherit from. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.inherit</key>
    <true/>
    <!-- Hardened-Runtime exceptions live on THIS binary's own signature and are
         COMPATIBLE with inherit (Apple forums/thread/706390 — HR exceptions are the
         inheritance-compatible family; only get-task-allow conflicts, and we don't
         set it). Do NOT add any App Sandbox resource entitlement (files.*, network.*)
         here — those would trip the _libsecinit_appsandbox abort under inherit. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
    <!-- Run-path transcription: numba/llvmlite JIT. See header comment +
         crash analysis (7 Jun 2026). Without these the sidecar SIGKILLs at
         the transcription stage under Hardened Runtime. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
